sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant GW as Istio/OpenShift Gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant KRBP as kube-rbac-proxy Sidecar<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Predictor as Predictor Container<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant StorageInit as Storage Initializer<br/>(init container)
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>(S3/GCS/Azure)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS

    Note over Client,Predictor: Flow 1: InferenceService Prediction (RawDeployment with Auth)

    Client->>GW: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    GW->>GW: HTTPRoute / VirtualService routing<br/>by hostname
    GW->>KRBP: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS 1.2+
    KRBP->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>Bearer Token validation
    K8sAPI-->>KRBP: Auth decision
    KRBP->>Predictor: Proxy to model server<br/>HTTP/8080 (pod-local)
    Predictor-->>KRBP: Prediction response
    KRBP-->>GW: HTTPS response
    GW-->>Client: JSON prediction result

    Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: LLMInferenceService Request (with InferencePool)

    participant Scheduler as Scheduler (EPP)<br/>9002/TCP HTTPS
    participant vLLM as vLLM Workload<br/>8080/TCP HTTPS

    Client->>GW: POST inference request<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+
    GW->>Scheduler: HTTPRoute -> InferencePool<br/>HTTPS/9002, TLS (self-signed)<br/>DestinationRule TLS SIMPLE
    Scheduler->>vLLM: Route to optimal pod<br/>HTTPS/8080, TLS (service-ca)<br/>DestinationRule TLS SIMPLE w/ CA
    vLLM-->>Scheduler: LLM response
    Scheduler-->>GW: Response
    GW-->>Client: JSON response

    Note over StorageInit,S3: Flow 3: Model Download (Storage Initializer)

    StorageInit->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>AWS IAM / GCS SA / Azure MSI
    S3-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts
    StorageInit->>StorageInit: Write to shared volume<br/>(emptyDir/PVC)
    Note right of StorageInit: Predictor reads model<br/>from shared volume

    Note over Client,Predictor: Flow 4: InferenceGraph Routing

    participant Router as kserve-router<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant ISvcA as InferenceService A<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    participant ISvcB as InferenceService B<br/>80/TCP HTTP

    Client->>GW: POST graph request<br/>HTTPS/443, Edge TLS
    GW->>Router: Forward to router<br/>HTTP/8080
    Router->>ISvcA: Step 1 inference<br/>HTTP/80 (in-mesh mTLS)
    ISvcA-->>Router: Intermediate result
    Router->>ISvcB: Step 2 inference<br/>HTTP/80 (in-mesh mTLS)
    ISvcB-->>Router: Final result
    Router-->>GW: Aggregated response
    GW-->>Client: JSON response
